Russia Is Producing 8,400 Tons of Beet Sugar Daily, Union Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-08-15T13:37:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/russia-is-producing-8-400-tons-of-beet-sugar-daily-union-says.html
Russia ’s daily sugar output from
domestic beets reached 8,400 metric tons, the Sugar Producers’
Union said on its  website  today.  A total of 18 plants, comprising 28 percent of national
sugar-refining capacity, are processing the crop, the group
said. Fourteen of the plants are located in the southern region
of Krasnodar, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  